President Barack Obama announced his intent to nominate David K. Mineta as the Deputy Director for Demand Reduction at the Office of National Drug Control Policy. Mineta currently serves as the Deputy Director of Asian American Recovery Services, Inc. and has extensive experience in behavioral health and substance abuse prevention. He also serves on the Jefferson Union High School District's Board of Trustees and the San Mateo First Five Commission. Mineta holds a Master's Degree in Social Work from San Jose State University and a Bachelor's Degree in Political Science from the University of California, Berkeley.

President Obama also announced his intent to appoint several individuals to serve on the Recovery Independent Advisory Panel. These individuals include Steven Koch, Vice Chairman and Co-Chairman of Credit Suisse's Mergers and Acquisitions Group; Chris Sale, Vice President for Development Finance at CHF International; Malcolm K. Sparrow, Professor of the Practice of Public Management at Harvard's Kennedy School of Government; and Edward Tufte, Professor Emeritus of Political Science, Statistics, and Computer Science at Yale University. Each appointee brings unique expertise in their respective fields and will contribute to the panel's efforts in advising on recovery and economic issues.